<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-04-02"><hi rend="italic">April 2,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Powell reports that everything is quiet, that the Syrian shops are
                            closed, and that the government is master of the situation.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>